docs.abstract: The technology research firm IDC predicts the pace of digital transformation of business is going to accelerate and increasingly hit every industry.
docs.snippet: The technology research firm IDC predicts the pace of digital transformation of business is going to accelerate and increasingly hit every industry.
docs.lead_paragraph: It is the time of year when the big technology research shops gaze into the near future to identify trends that will have the most impact on corporate America and the tech industry over the next few years.

headline.main: Digital Transformation Going Mainstream in 2016, IDC Predicts
headline.print_headline: Researchers Gaze Into the Tech Crystal Ball

docs.abstract: The tech stalwart has been hiring designers by the hundreds, all part of an accelerated approach to product development that is a major departure from the past.
docs.snippet: The tech stalwart has been hiring designers by the hundreds, all part of an accelerated approach to product development that is a major departure from the past.
docs.lead_paragraph: Phil Gilbert is a tall man with a shaved head and wire-rimmed glasses. He typically wears cowboy boots and bluejeans to work — hardly unusual these days, except he’s an executive at IBM, a company that still has a button-down suit-and-tie reputation. And in case you don’t get the message from his wardrobe, there’s a huge black-and-white photograph hanging in his office of a young Bob Dylan, hunched over sheet music, making changes to songs in the “Highway 61 Revisited” album. It’s an image, Mr. Gilbert will tell you, that conveys both a rebel spirit and hard work.

headline.main: IBM’s Design-Centered Strategy to Set Free the Squares

docs.abstract: A venerable technology company is adopting a strategy that moves it into disruptive systems.
docs.snippet: A venerable technology company is adopting a strategy that moves it into disruptive systems.
docs.lead_paragraph: Few companies – especially tech companies – can trace their history back more than a century.

headline.main: IBM Looks to Its Next Century

docs.abstract: Phil Gilbert, head of design at IBM, is trying to get the technology giant to embrace a new concept that could potentially help the company, which has seen two years of declining revenue, rethink its approach.
docs.snippet: Phil Gilbert, head of design at IBM, is trying to get the technology giant to embrace a new concept that could potentially help the company, which has seen two years of declining revenue, rethink its approach.
docs.lead_paragraph: IBM has been associated with many things over the years. But few people would ever connect Big Blue, as IBM is sometimes called, with a progressive attitude toward design.

headline.main: Daily Report: IBM Embraces Its Inner Designer

docs.abstract: Dr. Amdahl played a crucial role in developing the IBM System/360 series, which influenced computer design for years.

docs.lead_paragraph: Gene Amdahl, a trailblazer in the design of IBM’s mainframe computers, which became the central nervous system for businesses large and small throughout the world, died on Tuesday at a nursing home in Palo Alto, Calif. He was 92.

headline.main: Gene Amdahl, Pioneer of Mainframe Computing, Dies at 92
headline.print_headline: Gene Amdahl, Known at IBM as the Father of the Mainframe, Dies at 92
